President Barack Obama has proclaimed September 2012 as National Wilderness Month in the United States. In his proclamation, he highlights the importance of protected wilderness areas, which serve as recreational spaces, classrooms, laboratories, and historical treasures. These areas also provide clean air, clean water, and habitats for wildlife. Obama emphasizes the need to come together to protect these spaces for future generations. The President mentions his administration's efforts in designating wilderness areas and launching initiatives to engage Americans in conservation. He encourages all Americans to visit and enjoy wilderness areas, learn about their history, and contribute to their protection.